**Describe the bug**
After a users request has been authenticated  we would like to map the request to a specific user. After setting the span attribute `SEMATTRS_ENDUSER_ID` to the users ID it ID shows up under "Custom Properties" on the auth event. 

![Image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/2588f43f-7ec8-48bc-997b-4a9cf87f4d35)

Application insights also does not register this as a user in the user section.

How can I correctly set the user ID during authentication, ensure that it's included in subsequent events, and make sure the user appears in the User blade?

**To Reproduce**
Steps to reproduce the behavior:
1.  Setup trace expoter to azure and instrument some parts of the application like so 
  ```js
  if (process.env.APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING) {
    const currentServiceName = hostname() || 'backend';

    const sdk = new NodeSDK({
      resource: resourceFromAttributes({
        [ATTR_SERVICE_NAME]: currentServiceName,
      }),
      traceExporter: new AzureMonitorTraceExporter({
        connectionString: process.env.APPLICATIONINSIGHTS_CONNECTION_STRING,
      }),
      instrumentations: [
        new HttpInstrumentation({
          ignoreIncomingRequestHook(req) {
            // Ignore spans from /probes/health, /probes/ready, and /metrics
            return /^\/(probes\/(health|ready)|metrics)$/.test(req.url);
          },
        }),
        new ExpressInstrumentation(),
        new GraphQLInstrumentation(),
        new MongooseInstrumentation(),
        createAzureSdkInstrumentation(),
        new MongoDBInstrumentation({
          requireParentSpan: false,
        }),
      ],
    });

    try {
      sdk.start();
      console.log('Started tracing');
    } catch (error) {
      console.error(`Failed to start tracing. ${error}`);
    }

    process.on('SIGTERM', () => {
      sdk
        .shutdown()
        .then(() => console.log('Tracing terminated'))
        .catch((error) => console.log('Error terminating tracing', error))
        .finally(() => process.exit(0));
    });
  }

  ```
2. Added the span attribute in the auth middelware like so: 
  ```js
  import { context, trace } from '@opentelemetry/api';
  import { SEMATTRS_ENDUSER_ID } from '@opentelemetry/semantic-conventions';

  export const getAuthContext = async ({ tracer, getUserById }) => {
    const span = tracer.startSpan('auth.getAuthContext', undefined, context.active());

    try {
      return await context.with(trace.setSpan(context.active(), span), async () => {
        const user = await getUserById();
        if (user?.id) {
          span.setAttribute(SEMATTRS_ENDUSER_ID, user.id.toString());
        }
        return user;
      });
    } finally {
      span.end();
    }
  };
  ```

**Expected behavior**
I expect that application insights should be able to identify all the different authenticated users and then be able to map each request to a specific user 

**Screenshots**
N.A

**Additional context**
The client application is not instrumented at all and we are just getting the user data from the backend after they have authenticated

Environment Details:
SDK Version: @azure/search-documents@12.1.0
Node.js Version: v22.14.0 (Please confirm or update with your exact version: run node -v)
