## Describe the bug  
My app has a `process.on('multipleResolves', cb)` handler, which logs events from the `@azure/event-hubs` consumer each time messages are processed. While it doesnâ€™t cause functional issues, it clutters the logs.  

## To Reproduce  
Steps to reproduce the behavior:  
1. Create a minimal Node.js app with an Event Hubs consumer.  
2. Add `process.on('multipleResolves', cb)` to listen for multiple resolve events.  
3. Start receiving events from Event Hubs.  

## Expected behavior  
No `multipleResolves` events should be logged.  

## Screenshots  
<img width="1498" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/8a34a089-8082-41a7-a55b-7c33cbf36289" />

