**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I have a need to obtain a ACR refresh token suitable for use in invoking `helm` via the command line. For example, using the Azure CLI, I can run the following commands as described in [az acr login with --expose-token](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/container-registry/container-registry-authentication?tabs=azure-cli#az-acr-login-with---expose-token):
```sh
TOKEN=$(az acr login --name <acrName> --expose-token --output tsv --query accessToken)
echo $TOKEN | helm registry login myregistry.azurecr.io \
            --username 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000 \
            --password-stdin
```

I would like to be able to generate a similar token using the JavaScript SDK.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
Ideally, I would like to call `getToken` or `getRefreshToken` directory from the [ContainerRegistryClient](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/javascript/api/@azure/container-registry/containerregistryclient?view=azure-node-latest) class. Ideally, this could look something like:
```javascript
const AzIdentity = require('@azure/identity');
const AzContainerRegistry = require('@azure/container-registry');

const creds = new AzIdentity.DefaultAzureCredential();
const client = new AzContainerRegistry.ContainerRegistryClient('https://myregistry.azurecr.io', creds);
const token = await client.getRefreshToken();
```

**Describe alternatives you've considered**
Having looked at the code, this seems to be possible today by access the internal [AuthenticationImpl](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-js/blob/main/sdk/containerregistry/container-registry/src/generated/operations/authentication.ts) class, but requires the user to understand the inner workings of the ACR authentication token exchange flow and the fact that the refresh token is what is actually needed by helm (not an access token). Additionally, this means that there does not seem to be any need to go through the entire challenge flow. The following produces a refresh token that allows successful login using `docker login` or `helm repository login`:

```javascript
const AzIdentity = require('@azure/identity');
const AzContainerRegistry = require('@azure/container-registry');

const creds = new AzIdentity.DefaultAzureCredential();
const client = new AzContainerRegistry.ContainerRegistryClient('https://myregistry.azurecr.io', creds);
const authClient = client.client.authentication;
const aadAccessToken = await azCreds.getToken("https://containerregistry.azure.net/.default");
const acrRefreshToken = await authClient.exchangeAadAccessTokenForAcrRefreshToken(
  'access_token',
  'myregistry.azurecr.io', {
    accessToken: aadAccessToken.token,
  }
);
```

Since `az acr login` is exposed directly from the Azure CLI, I think this could be generally useful to be exposed via the JavaScript SDK and would avoid having to utilize the internal AuthenticationImpl class.

